{
  "answer": "**The line \"Cheen o Arab hamara, Hindustaan hamara\" (often transliterated or quoted as \"Cheen-o-Arab hamara, Hindostan hamara\") is the opening couplet of Allama Iqbal's poem *Tarana-e-Milli* (\"The Anthem of the Community\" or \"National Song\"), found in *Bang-e-Dara Part 3*.**[^1]\n\nThis famous patriotic verse expresses Muslim unity across the world, beginning:\n\n> Cheen o Arab hamara, Hindustaan hamara  \n> Muslim hain hum, watan hai saara jahan hamara[^1]\n\nIn the original Urdu script:\n\n> چین و عرب ہمارا، ہندوستان ہمارا  \n> مسلم ہیں ہم، وطن ہے سارا جہاں ہمارا[^2]\n\nAnd in English translation:\n\n> From Chin to Arab lands, our story flows,  \n> The whole wide world's the home a Muslim knows.[^3]\n\nThis poem, part of Iqbal's 1924 collection *Bang-e-Dara* (The Call of the Bell), celebrates Islamic brotherhood transcending national boundaries.[^4]\n\n[^1]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 3*, ch. 23 \"Tarana-e-Milli\" (transliteration), [p-56247d](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-3-cc61e8/23-tarana-e-milli/transliteration/#p-56247d).\n[^2]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 3*, ch. 23 \"Tarana-e-Milli\" (original), [p-c093d8](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-3-cc61e8/23-tarana-e-milli/original/#p-c093d8).\n[^3]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 3*, ch. 23 \"Tarana-e-Milli\" (translation), [p-8a4681](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-3-cc61e8/23-tarana-e-milli/translation/#p-8a4681).\n[^4]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 3*, ch. 23 \"Tarana-e-Milli\" (translation), [/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-3-cc61e8/23-tarana-e-milli/translation/](https://falsafa.corpus/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-3-cc61e8/23-tarana-e-milli/translation/).",
